\begin_layout Subsection
Retrieving data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Users may select from previously populated values in the combo-box.
 Users may also freehand type the value into the box and it will suggest
 a possible value which they may accept by pressing enter.
 Pressing enter is also required if fully typing the chosen country.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Refreshing data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Data can be refreshed using the appropriately marked refresh ( ↻ ) button.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Offline use
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
TriCovid must have an initial internet connection to fetch data.
 While technically afterwards you could operate offline with that data,
 it is recommended to not do that.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Troubleshooting issues
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If TriCovid is ran from the console you can view extended information, should
 a bug occur.
 In normal operation this should not be necessary.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Moral issues
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The biggest potential moral issue I see is that users could have outdated
 information and not realise it.
 I'm not sure if there is necessarily an easy solution to such an issue,
 however displaying the information date may at least help.
 For this reason offline use is not a feature.
\end_layout

